        Run Look ### Run a Look. Runs a given look's query and returns the results in the requested format. Supported formats: | result_format | Description | :-----------: | :--- | | json | Plain json | json_detail | Row data plus metadata describing the fields, pivots, table calcs, and other aspects of the query | csv | Comma separated values with a header | txt | Tab separated values with a header | html | Simple html | md | Simple markdown | xlsx | MS Excel spreadsheet | sql | Returns the generated SQL rather than running the query | png | A PNG image of the visualization of the query | jpg | A JPG image of the visualization of the query
        Parameters:
        lookId - Id of look (required)
        resultFormat - Format of result (required)
        limit - Row limit (may override the limit in the saved query). (optional)
        applyFormatting - Apply model-specified formatting to each result. (optional)
        applyVis - Apply visualization options to results. (optional)
        cache - Get results from cache if available. (optional)
        imageWidth - Render width for image formats. (optional)
        imageHeight - Render height for image formats. (optional)
        generateDrillLinks - Generate drill links (only applicable to 'json_detail' format. (optional)
        forceProduction - Force use of production models even if the user is in development mode. (optional)
        cacheOnly - Retrieve any results from cache even if the results have expired. (optional)
        pathPrefix - Prefix to use for drill links (url encoded). (optional)
        rebuildPdts - Rebuild PDTS used in query. (optional)
        serverTableCalcs - Perform table calculations on query results (optional)
        Returns:
        String
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
